tip.text: Wow. Finally. Good coffee.
Not bad. Am usually quite wary when it comes to local Singaporean cuisine but this didn't disappoint. I even finished all the soup!

tip.text: Meh. Super meh.

formattedAddress: Marina Bay Link Mall (8A Marina Boulevard #B2-46)

tip.text: The chilli crabs aren't too bad. (And I generally never like Singapore Chili Crab sauce)

formattedAddress: #01-07/08, East Coast Seafood Centre (1206 East Coast Parkway)

venue.name: Jumbo Seafood Restaurant 珍宝海鮮樓

tip.text: Yes. Yes. Yes. Starfruit gin was amazing. Fresh oysters were amazing. Finger food to die for. Plenty of speciality alcohol from the States, you could go mad trying them all. Big love to the staff too.

formattedAddress: B1-08, Ocean Financial Centre (10 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: The most adorable desserts. Quite yummy too but hella pricy for what you get.
We ordered their platter, most of their desserts and the house cab sav. SO GOOD. Hands down one of the best meals I've had in Singapore.
Try the truffle one or the carne. Soft and fluffy base with fresh toppings. Yum yum, this place is superior to other pizza places in KL.
We had their waygu and duck breast which were both pretty good. V yum charcoal pavlova (I usually detest desserts). It's also a relatively casual and comfortable setting. Would definitely go back.
Super chilled place to hang out but beware of the numerous flies. Take out boxes aren't very environmentally friendly IMO but the food is good and two huge thumbs up for the delicious cup of coffee .
Order their Chicken chop, pork chop or their roti babi and take a trip to Heaven.

contact.facebookName: 镒记茶餐室 Yut Kee (1928), Jalan Dang Wangi

tip.text: Hmm. Huge portions at affordable prices (it costs less than RM15 and three people could share one nicely). Pretty cosy place. But it's really just shaved ice, guys. Nothing too dreamy and spectacular.
So. Not. Worth. The. Hype.

If you're looking for good g & t around the area, Mercat is definitely the place to go. Absolutely fantastic service from waiters who truly know their stuff. Pricy bt they hve great deals on weekends.

Waitress explained to us what every other dish was on the menu. We were obviously local, so slightly offensive that a non-local tried to explain our cuisine! VERY disappointed with their g&t! Food=OK.
Delicious, delicious, delicious w lovely ambience! Enjoyed their masak asam, sambal sotong & sambal belacan. Ice cream w fermentedrice is really good (exactly like rum ice cream, but non alcoholic!).
Yum yum yum. Friendly service, affordable service and delicious food!
I really enjoyed the ikan bakar and wild boar rendang. The other tapas were good too, although not such a fan of the Singaporean chilli prawns. But most importantly, such WONDERFUL service!
Yes, please. Yum yum yum Idli at deliciously affordable prices.
Their wagyu steak is REALLY good and affordable for the generous portions. Pairs well with their house wine. So glad I've found this place!
Authentic and affordable Vietnamese food! I really enjoyed the pho. The pork skewers and spring rolls were OK but real cheap for what you get. Please try the pho though. It's so delicious.

contact.facebookName: Ara Vietnamese Noodles 越南小吃 Nhà hàng Việt Nam

tip.text: It's okay. Average food. Okay-Coffee. But it's a very nice place.

formattedAddress: 50000 Kuala Lumpur City Center, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Affordable yummy food, delicious craft beer, and friendly staff. The deco/ambience is fancy enough without being too pretentious. I will definitely be back to try more!!! PS/ Love the Asian Wings!

formattedAddress: First Floor Tropicana Avenue (Persiaran Tropicana , Jalan Tr 2/5)

tip.text: Surprised to finally find good fresh juicy mussels. The legendary laksa is to die for. Yum yum. Lovely cosy ambience too.

formattedAddress: 59000 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Yum generous salads. Try the goodness greens dressing and the goodness greens drink! But was disappointed with the service as it was slow, a little rude and they got our order wrong.

location.neighborhood: Taman Tun Doktor Ismail, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Horrible acoustics when packed, w slow service. But the chicken & waffles were good and HUGE portions for the price. Note: Masala shrimp wrap didn't have enough shrimp. Would go back again regardless
I really don't like the deco of this place but they have good steaks at a good price.
Terrible service, very loud music and only mediocre drinks. It's a nice place though and a good location. Real pity they haven't sorted themselves out yet.
Yes, please! Best burger and fries in Bangsar. My favourite is the one with the cornflakes.
ABSOLUTE YUM
They play golden oldies and serve yummy chicken rice. It's also pretty cool and shaded too.
Best steak I've had in awhile!! Hands down. Absolutely love this place. Casual setting, affordable prices. I'll come here again and again.
I'm nvr usually impressed w most dessert places in KL (despite my ❤ for gelato) bt this one deserves a shout-out fr bng sch a friendly place & hving delicious gelato!  chilli ginger lemongrass = wow
Honest, comfort food at very affordable prices. Lots of love.

formattedAddress: Plaza Damansara (Jalan Medan Setia 2, Bukit Damansara)

tip.text: I love to hang out here after a long day at work. Waiters can recommend wine well without being too pretentious. Food is always delicious too. Yay!

formattedAddress: G133, Bangsar Shopping Centre (289 Jalan Maarof)

tip.text: Comforting, as soup noodles are supposed to be..but the spicy noodle soup wasn't very spicy (to me) and very, very oily. Worth checking out though if you enjoy soup noodles.

location.address: 61-P1, Block D, The School, Jaya One

venue.name: Go Noodle House 有間麵館

tip.text: This place is like an awkward adolescent trying too hard without knowing wt it wants to be. Food was bad, seats were uncomfortable, ambience was pathetic. Good news- I know I won't have to come back.
BEST PAN MEE EVER. I swear guys, this is what true love tastes like.

venue.name: Restoran Super Kitchen Chilli Pan Mee

tip.text: Lemongrass gelato was subtle and nice, but also try their basil flavoured gelato. Nice place to chill if you manage to get a seat!
Biasa aja. But the simplicity and friendliness was comforting nonetheless. Pricey though, as it is located at a rather touristy area!!
Everything is good here!! My only suggestion is to also order their tamarind drink because it makes you ☺ in ways you never knew you could be.
My squid ink baguette was solid hard like a rock. Sorry, but despite the friendly service, wonderful ambience and tempting treats, I unfortunately wasn't impressed.
The Kong Bak Pau (or Asian Sliders) were so yum yum delicious and at only $7.50. It definitely matched well with their smooth (albeit mediocre-tasting) coffee. Friendly service too, love this place!
Fun place with friendly staff! My cup of Catwoman caramel latte came in a cup with a cape!

formattedAddress: #01-03/04/05, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands (2 Bayfront Avenue)
location.address: #01-03/04/05, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

contact.facebookName: DC Comics Super Heroes Cafe - Official

tip.text: Squid Ink Paella and Patatas Gratas. Always. So good. Their meat and cheese platter is good too. Love this place!
Cosy take out place. Lemon meringue tart was good but too sweet for me. Lovely people, I'd come back to try more things.
We didn't really like their coffee (I had mine with soy and could only taste the soy) so won't be coming back but its a decent place to chill, away from the hustle and bustle.
The pork chop tastes like warm, fuzzy childhood memories. Mmmm! Simple, quick and good.

venue.name: Restaurant Sin Kee (新记(中西)餐室)

tip.text: Fresh sashimi, good service, small cosy place. Nothing too impressive though.
Ox Tongue Rice (Mirin Sauce) and Fried Oysters were good. Incredibly cosy place although tad overpriced. Interesting menu though, check it out if you ever manage to find parking around here!
I wouldn't nominate this place as having the best burgers around town, and would probably only come back as their boozy shakes are rather tempting! OK-burgers, fun place.

formattedAddress: Lot 30, Level G2, Publika Shopping Gallery, No. 1, Jalan Dutamas 1, Solaris Dutamas
location.address: Lot 30, Level G2, Publika Shopping Gallery, No. 1, Jalan Dutamas 1, Solaris Dutamas

tip.text: We waited for an hour ++ and were disappointed with our steaks. Try the sticky toffee pudding and Blackmore wagyu if you're willing to experience an exceptionally long wait.
